{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d2cb5631-b44c-4f2a-bba7-8b78f82dc167","content":"No files exist yet. Since there's no existing code, here's exactly what you need:\n\n## Compiled Bindings with `x:DataType`\n\nAdd the `x:DataType` attribute to your `ContentPage`, pointing at your ViewModel's CLR namespace. This tells the XAML compiler to resolve bindings at compile time instead of using reflection at runtime.\n\n**Before (interpreted bindings):**\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             x:Class=\"MyApp.Views.SettingsPage\">\n    <StackLayout>\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Slider Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n    </StackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n**After (compiled bindings):**\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"MyApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n    <StackLayout>\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Slider Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n    </StackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nTwo changes:\n1. **`xmlns:vm`** — imports the ViewModel's namespace.\n2. **`x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"`** — enables compiled bindings against that type.\n\n## Catching binding errors at build time\n\nWith `x:DataType` in place, misspelled or missing properties (e.g. `{Binding Themee}`) become **compile errors**, not silent runtime failures.\n\nTo enforce this strictly, add to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nThis promotes XAML binding warnings to errors so the build fails on any mismatch.\n\n### Tips\n- You can set `x:DataType` on **any element**, not just the page root — useful when a `DataTemplate` binds to a different type.\n- To opt out for a specific binding (e.g. a `RelativeSource` or ancestor binding), use `x:DataType=\"{x:Null}\"` locally.\n- The ViewModel still needs to be assigned at runtime via `BindingContext = new SettingsViewModel();` — `x:DataType` only provides compile-time type info.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"11119738-59a5-4e2f-b921-16c9fbbfbcf0","outputTokens":688,"requestId":"DBD4:19AB05:84C87:A5387:69F549F2"},"id":"e8d5a4c8-00e8-43fc-973e-66facde295b7","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:49:03.990Z","parentId":"af3dc73e-b078-40f6-8d73-92bf53c3f4f1"}
